Texas-San Antonio, VCU Win to Complete 1st Round of NCAA Men’s Tournament

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-03-17T04:21:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/texas-san-antonio-vcu-win-to-complete-1st-round-of-ncaa-men-s-tournament.html
The University of Texas-San Antonio
and Virginia Commonwealth University won first-round games in
college basketball’s national men’s championship.  UTSA defeated Alabama State University 70-61 and VCU beat
the  University of Southern California  59-46 last night in the
National Collegiate Athletic Association tournament.  Full tournament play begins today with 16 second-round
games at four sites. The field was expanded to 68 teams this
year, with four schools eliminated in the first round.  UTSA next will play  Ohio State University , the top overall
seed and No. 1 in the East Regional. VCU will play Georgetown,
the sixth seed in the Southwest Regional. Both games are
tomorrow.  Melvin Johnson III led the UTSA Roadrunners (20-13) with 29
points at the University of Dayton Arena in Dayton,  Ohio .
Jeffery Middlebrooks and Tramayne Moorer were high scorers for
the Alabama State Hornets (17-18) with 12 points each.  Jamie Skeen led the VCU Rams (24-11) with 16 points, while
Jio Fontan scored 14 points for the USC Trojans (19-15).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
